         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Argus Hotel Melbourne, ¶ 9. July 1857. ¶ My dear Mr Gregory. ¶  ¶ Some difference in opinion has arisen between some of my scientific friends as to the origin of the drawings seen by Sir George Gray o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">57.07.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Augustus Gregory</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS Q442 inward correspondence, Gregory papers, Dixson Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Argus Hotel Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9. July 1857.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mr Gregory.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Some difference in opinion has arisen between some of my scientific friends as to the origin of the drawings seen by Sir George Gray on the N. W. coast. As you have read the work of Gray,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Grey (1841), see vol. 1, chapters 9, 11.</p>
               </note> please would you favor me with your opinion, whether these are to be regarded as the work of the natives or as the work of an other race.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have in accordance with your request, instantly prepared the triplicate of my report,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B58.05.01. See A. Gregory to M, 13 June 1857, and M to A. Gregory, 18 June 1857.</p>
               </note> which I hope arrived in due time.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my sincere wishes for your welfare, I remain,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">dear Sir, your obed. servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">A. C. Gregory Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
         </div>
      </body>
